OL,6,F"Their voices which were silenced as
OL,7,Fdefenceless children, even those whose
OL,8,Fparents tried to stand up against the
OL,9,Fbarrage of brutality, are being heard
OL,10,Fand their bravery in reliving such
OL,11,Fterrible memories is testament to a
OL,12,Fnational trauma which must be
OL,13,Facknowledged."
